Slip rings with through bores are specially engineered electrical slip rings that incorporate a central hollow shaft, enabling the passage of rotating axles, pipelines or fluid lines while simultaneously transmitting power, signals or data between stationary and moving parts. This architecture provides high space efficiency and reduces overall system weight, making it ideal for rotary platforms such as wind‑turbine nacelles, industrial‑automation robots, medical imaging equipment and radar antennas. Because the hollow bore accommodates mechanical components directly through the slip‑ring assembly, designers can achieve tighter packaging without compromising reliability or electrical performance.
